<item>
            <title>[LU-11007] Upgrading Lustre 2.8fe to 2.10.x - on-disk format change question</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11007</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Are there on-disk format changes between Lustre 2.8fe and Lustre 2.10.x, even if one avoids use of new features to 2.10 like PFL and project quota, and avoids DNE2?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IE if we were to mount a Lustre 2.8fe file system with Lustre 2.10 kernel modules, and perform some mdtests and IORs, would there be on-disk changes that prevent the file system from being mounted again with 2.8fe kernel modules?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the answer different for ldiskfs than for ZFS backend?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The context would be performing tests before releasing the file system to users, after upgrading the software from 2.8fe to 2.10.x., and falling back to 2.8fe if the tests reveal a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="52153">LU-11007</key>
            <summary>Upgrading Lustre 2.8fe to 2.10.x - on-disk format change question</summary>
